frechet distance¶

In [18]:
from similaritymeasures import frechet_dist, dtw, pcm, area_between_two_curves

# create a list to store the distances

# loop through the defectos list
def matrix_frechet_dist(defectos, column):
    distances = []
    t = np.linspace(0, 1, len(defectos[0][column]))
    for i in range(len(defectos)):
        current_distances = []
        for j in range(len(defectos)):
            # calculate the Frechet distance between the current element and the j-th element
            distance = frechet_dist([t,defectos[i][column]], [t,defectos[j][column]])
            # append the distance to the current_distances list
            current_distances.append(distance)
        # append the current_distances list to the distances list
        distances.append(current_distances)
    return distances

correlación cruzada¶

In [21]:
# create a list to store the correlations
correlations = []

# loop through the defectos list
for i in range(len(defectos)):
    current_correlations = []
    for j in range(len(defectos)):
        # calculate the cross correlation between the current element and the j-th element
        correlation = np.correlate(defectos[i]['Filtered Signal'], defectos[j]['Filtered Signal'], mode='same')
        # append the correlation to the current_correlations list
        current_correlations.append(correlation)
    # append the current_correlations list to the correlations list
    correlations.append(current_correlations)
